Six people were killed in separate attacks in Bakin Kogi and Kaninkon in Jamaa  local government area of Kaduna state yesterday. The two separate attacks were said to have been perpetuated about 10am and 11am by yet to be identified gunmen. A member of the security committee in the community who confirmed the attacks on telephone to newsmen, said the gunmen, numbering about 10, were wearing army and mobile police uniforms. He said three people were killed in the bush when they went to cut wood for the roofing of their houses while three others were killed at a local mining site. The Kaduna Police Public Relations Officer, ASP  Mukhtar Hussaini, said the dead comprised four males and two females. He said the police had commenced efforts to arrest those behind the attacks.